# Menu

A IDS menu is a temporary list that is revealed upon a user’s interaction with a button, icon, or other control, which allows users to access a group of choices and/or actions.

This is used primarily in our other IDS components, such as `Dropdown`, `DropdownButton`, and `SplitButton`.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/menu
```

```tsx
import { Menu, MenuItem } from '@ids-ts/menu';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `accessStringMatch` | `string` | No | Key to match string |
| `alignment` | `Alignments` | No | Alignment for the Menu: vertical (`'top'`, `'bottom'`, `'middle'`), horizontal (`'left'`, `'right'`, `'center'`). |
| `anchorElement` | `React.ReactElement` | Yes | The element used to set the position of showing the Menu. |
| `autoFocus` | `boolean` | No | Whether the menu should auto-focus on open. |
| `children` | `ReactElement<MenuItemProps> \| ReactElement<MenuItemProps>[]` | No | Menu contents, normally `MenuItem` components. |
| `className` | `string` | No | Class to be assigned to Menu. Use to extend the style. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `disableSearch` | `boolean` | No | - |
